From 458d0524ab04837f3f974839db620b4446da123a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude Fleet <fleet@factorylm.local>
Date: Sat, 4 Jul 2026 11:40:12 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] fix(web): durable Stripe->Hub provisioning with retry +
 idempotency

The webhook's hub_users bridge was best-effort: if the customer paid
before registering on the Hub (UPDATE matched 0 rows) or the hub DB
call threw, the paying customer stayed unprovisioned with no retry.

- new plg_pending_hub_provisioning table (quota.ensureSchema), keyed
  on the Stripe event id: ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING makes Stripe event
  redelivery a no-op, and the underlying hub_users UPDATE is itself
  idempotent, so replays can never double-provision
- webhook (checkout.session.completed / customer.subscription.deleted)
  queues a pending record on matched=0 or error, and closes queued
  records once a delivery lands
- reconcilePendingHubProvisioning() retries pending rows; hooked
  fire-and-forget into /api/magic/login and the /api/register
  returning-active path, and exposed as POST
  /api/admin/hub-provisioning/reconcile (x-admin-token) for cron
- tests follow the mocked-neon pattern of hub-user-activation.test.ts

Verified: bun test (15/15 pass incl. 9 new; full suite 295 pass /
20 fail identical to pre-change baseline) and tsc --noEmit (33 errors
before and after, all pre-existing dep-drift; 0 in touched files).
